## conda
wget https://repo.continuum.io/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
chmod +x Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
./Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh

## python packages
conda install mamba scipy matplotlib imageio ipython flake8 pylint autopep8 black sympy pandas tqdm rich powerline-status pygit2 -c pytorch -c nvidia -c conda-forge -c default

Useful tools + vim ALE/YCM + powerline

## chrome
Download from chrome site.
sudo dpkg -i google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install google-chrome-stable

## fish
sudo apt-add-repository ppa:fish-shell/release-3
sudo apt update
sudo apt install fish

We can't set the default shell with `chsh`, since we are using LDAP.
But the dotfiles should enable fish in Terminator and tmux.

## vim, vim-gtk needed for X11 clipboard
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:jonathonf/vim
sudo apt update
sudo apt install vim vim-gtk3

## vim plugins
curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim

Run PlugInstall in vim to install plugins listed in .vimrc

## git
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:git-core/ppa
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git

cd /usr/share/doc/git/contrib/diff-highlight/
sudo make

